			<CASNumber>10026-24-1</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Cobalt(II) sulfate heptahydrate, also known as Cobaltous sulfate heptahydrate, is a compound that may cause nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, vasodilatation, mild hypotension, rash and ringing in the ears upon ingestion. It can cause irritation, redness and pain on skin or eye contact. Skin contact may also result in allergic reactions. Other symptoms include headache and nervous system disturbances. It appears as pink or red crystals, is stable, non-flammable, and hygroscopic and undergoes dehydration at 41°C and 71°C.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">七水硫酸钴（又称七水硫酸钴）是一种化合物，摄入后可能会引起恶心、呕吐、腹痛、血管扩张、轻度低血压、皮疹和耳鸣。皮肤或眼睛接触后会出现刺激、发红和疼痛。皮肤接触也可能导致过敏反应。其他症状包括头痛和神经系统紊乱。它呈粉红色或红色晶体，性质稳定，不易燃，具有吸湿性，在 41°C 和 71°C 温度下会脱水。</common:generalComment>
